1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,000
Let me briefly walk you through the project structure

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:10,000
The main entry point is run_pipeline py

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:12,500
which runs the full workflow

4
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:14,000
from ingestion

5
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:15,500
to formatting

6
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:16,500
combination

7
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:18,000
and indexing

8
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:24,000
The jobs folder contains most of the project logic

9
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:27,000
starting with the ingestion folder

10
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:30,000
that collects raw data from the music and weather APIs

11
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:36,000
The formatting folder cleans the raw JSON and converts it into Parquet

12
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:42,000
while the combination folder joins music and weather data by region and date

13
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:47,000
It then calculates the City Depression Index

14
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:52,000
and the indexing folder sends the combined result to Elasticsearch

15
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:57,000
The data folder works like a small data lake

16
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:59,000
with three layers

17
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:00,500
raw

18
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:02,500
formatted

19
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:05,000
and combined

20
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:09,500
The raw layer keeps the original API responses

21
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:14,000
the formatted layer stores cleaned Parquet files

22
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:18,000
and the combined layer stores the final joined data

23
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:24,000
The dags folder contains the Airflow DAG

24
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:29,000
which shows how the pipeline can be scheduled automatically

25
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:35,000
The docker folder has the Docker Compose file for Elasticsearch and Kibana

26
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:41,000
and the kibana folder stores the exported dashboard configuration

27
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:47,000
The dashboard folder contains a standalone HTML version

28
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:52,000
of the visualization that works without opening Kibana

29
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:53,000
Overall

30
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:55,500
the project follows a standard data pipeline

31
00:01:55,500 --> 00:01:56,500
collect

32
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:57,500
clean

33
00:01:57,500 --> 00:01:58,500
join

34
00:01:58,500 --> 00:01:59,500
calculate CDI

35
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:00,000
and visualize the result
